<p><strong>Languages</strong> Giant, Orc</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 4 (1,100 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Two Heads.</em></strong> The ettin has advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks and on saving throws against being blinded, charmed, deafened, frightened, stunned, and knocked unconscious.</p>

<p><strong><em>Wakeful.</em></strong> When one of the ettinâ€™s heads is asleep, its other head is awake.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Multiattack.</em></strong> The ettin makes two attacks: one with its battleaxe and one with its morningstar.</p>

<p><strong><em>Battleaxe.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +7 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 14 (2d8 + 5) slashing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Morningstar.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +7 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 14 (2d8 + 5) piercing damage.</p>

